==Starting the Event==
===Talking to the [[Bartender (Blue Moon Inn)]] before starting the event===
* '''Bartender:''' If you're here to offer us a hand during the festive rush, please talk to the cook in the kitchen!
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|event=no|A glass of your finest ale please.}}
* {{topt|event=no|Can you recommend where an adventurer might make his fortune?}}
* {{topt|event=no|Do you know where I can get some good equipment?}}

===Talking to the cook===
* {{tselect|Ask about the Christmas Event?}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** '''Cook:''' Can't you see the huge queue of people? I really don't have time to chat.
** '''Player:''' Oh, sorry, I thought I could lend you a hand?
** '''Cook:''' Really?! Oh thank the Gods!
** {{tcond|If the player doesn't have a serving platter and has no free inventory space:}}
*** '''Cook:''' Come back when you've got some space to carry a serving tray.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player doesn't have a serving platter and has 1 free inventory space:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=serving platter detail.png|The Cook hands you a serving platter.}}
*** {{tact|receives=a [[Serving platter]]}}
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Cook:''' Now, head in to the bar, greet whoever's at the front of the queue, and show them to an empty table.
** '''Cook:''' I'll be back here cooking up whatever needs cooking if you get a little lost or need some guidance.
** '''Cook:''' Got it?
** '''Player:''' Got it...
** '''Player:''' Will I be getting paid for this?
** '''Cook:''' Wow, really...?
** '''Cook:''' Look, legally I can't pay you because you technically don't work here, but how about I cook you a Christmas dinner at the end of your shift?
** '''Player:''' Free food? Count me in!
** '''Cook:''' Fantastic! Now go deal with that queue!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|event=no|No}}

===Talking to the cook after losing the serving tray===
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** '''Cook:''' Come back when you've got some space to carry a serving tray.
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Player:''' I seem to have lost that serving platter you gave me.
* '''Cook:''' Not a problem, here's a new one.
* {{tcond|If the player does not have a food order that needs to be cooked:}}
** '''Player:''' Sorry to bother you, but what was I meant to be doing again?
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tcond|If the player has a food order that needs to be cooked:}}
** '''Player:''' I have a food order!
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tcond|If the player has completed all the food orders:}}
** '''Cook:''' Good job, kid. That's your shift done!
** {{tact|continue}}

===Talking to the cook before greeting a customer===
* '''Player:''' Sorry to bother you, but what was I meant to be doing again?
* '''Cook:''' Go greet whoever is at the front of the queue.
* '''Player:''' Yes boss!
* {{tact|end}}

